{"lemma": "سِبْطٌ", "slug": "سِبْطٌ", "root": "س.ب.ط", "root_slug": "س-ب-ط", "root_link": "/words/roots/س-ب-ط", "pos": "N", "pos_camel": "noun", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": false}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 5, "pos_tags": ["adj", "noun", "verb"], "has_etymology": true, "sense_count": 15}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n18726"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%90%D8%A8%D9%92%D8%B7%D9%8C"}}, "translations": {"en": "grandchild", "fa": "نوه", "ur": "پوتا", "tr": "torun", "id": "cucu", "bn": "নাতী", "es": "nieto", "fr": "petit-enfant", "de": "Enkel", "ru": "внук", "zh": "孙子"}, "definition": {"source": "wiktextract", "senses": [{"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to be lanky"}, {"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to be well-shaped, to be graceful"}, {"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to be liberal, to be bountiful, to be munificent, to be generous"}, {"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to miscarry"}, {"pos": "adj", "gloss": "lanky"}, {"pos": "adj", "gloss": "well-shaped, graceful"}, {"pos": "adj", "gloss": "liberal, bountiful, munificent, generous"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "buffelgrasses (Cenchrus gen. et spp.)", "tags": ["collective"]}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "Stipagrostis spp.", "tags": ["collective"]}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "grandchild from the mother's side"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "grandchild"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "tribe of the Israelites"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "Shia imam (grandchild of the prophet)", "examples": [{"text": "أَيُّهَا النَّاسُ أُعْطِينَا سِتًّا وَفُضِّلْنَا بِسَبْعٍ أُعْطِينَا الْعِلْمَ وَالْحِلْمَ وَالسَّمَاحَةَ وَالْفَصَاحَةَ وَالشَّجَاعَةَ وَالْمَحَبَّةَ فِي قُلُوبِ الْمُؤْمِنِينَ وَفُضِّلْنَا بِأَنَّ مِنَّا النَّبِيَّ الْمُخْتَارَ مُحَمَّدًا وَمِنَّا الصِّدِيقَ وَمِنَّا الطَّيَارَ وَمِنَّا أَسَدَ اللهِ وَأَسَدَ رَسُولِهِ وَمِنَّا سِبْطَا هٰذِهِ الْأُمَّةِ مَنْ عَرَفَنِي فَقَدْ عَرَفَنِي وَمَنْ لَمْ يَعْرِفْنِي أَنْبَأْتُهُ بِحَسَبِيّ وَنَسَبِيّ"}]}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "Shia imam (grandchild of the prophet); al-Ḥusayn ibn ʿAlī or al-Ḥasan ibn ʿAlī", "tags": ["definite", "especially"]}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "wand, staff", "tags": ["rare"]}]}, "etymology": {"source": "wiktextract", "text": "Inherited from Proto-Semitic *šabṭ- (literally “staff, rod”). Semantically influenced by Hebrew שֵׁבֶט (śeḇeṭ, “tribe of Israel; staff, sceptre”)."}, "ipa": null, "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n18726", "headword_ar": "سِبْطٌ", "root": "sbT", "body": [{"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A grandchild;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, Msb, K;)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a son's child,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a daughter's child:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M, TA:) pl."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^asobaATN", "text_ar": "اَسْبَاطٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (S, Msb, TA;) which is commonly used by the vulgar as signifying"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "daughters' children;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "distinguished by them from"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aHofaAdN", "text_ar": "اَحْفَادٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[which they apply to son's children, pl. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HafiydN", "text_ar": "حَفِيدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; but the leading lexicologists expressly declare that it includes sons' children and daughters' children, as it is said to do by ISd: IAar explained"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "siboTN", "text_ar": "سِبْطٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "siboTaAni", "text_ar": "سِبْطَانِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^asobaATN", "text_ar": "اَسْبَاطٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as signifying the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "particularly distinguished,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "choicest, of children."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.) It is said in a trad., (TA,)"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlHasanu waAlHusayonu siboTaA rasuwli A@ll~`hi", "text_ar": "الحَسَنُ وَالحُسَيْنُ سِبْطَا رَسُولِ ا@للّٰهِ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "El-Hasan, and El-Hoseyn are the two grandsons of the Apostle of God."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M, TA. *) ―         -b2-"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A tribe of the Jews:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "pl."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^asobaATN", "text_ar": "اَسْبَاطٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (M, Msb, K:)"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "siboTN", "text_ar": "سِبْطٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^asobaATN", "text_ar": "اَسْبَاطٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, Msb) in relation to the Jews, (M, Msb,) or [rather] the Children of Israel, (S,) being like"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qabiylapN", "text_ar": "قَبِيلَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qabaAy^ilu", "text_ar": "قَبَايِلُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, Msb) in relation to the Arabs: (S, M, Msb:) and the former are thus called to distinguish them from the children of Ishmael. (M, TA.) In the phrase,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "waqaT~aEonaAhumu A@vonataYo", "text_ar": "وَقَطَّعْنَاهُمُ ا@ثْنَتَىْ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Ea$orapa A^asobaATFA", "text_ar": "عَشْرَةَ اَسْبَاطًا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "And we divided them into twelve"}, {"kind": "page_break", "n": 1295}, {"kind": "text", "text": "divisions,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "tribes"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "], (S, M, K,) in the Kur [vii. 160], (S, M,)"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AsbATA", "text_ar": "اسباطا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is a substitute (S, M, K) for"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AvntY", "text_ar": "اثنتى"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "E$rp", "text_ar": "عشرة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, M,) not a specificative, (S, M, K,) because the specificative may only be a sing.; (S, M;) the meaning being"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wqT~EnAhm AvntY E$rp firoqapF", "text_ar": "وقطّعناهم اثنتى عشرة فِرْقَةً"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AsbATFA", "text_ar": "اسباطًا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Akh, Zj, S,) and therefore the numeral is fem.; (Akh, S;) or this is a mistake; for it should be"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "firaqFA AvntY E$rp", "text_ar": "فِرَقًا اثنتى عشرة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; and therefore the numeral is fem. (Abu-l-'Abbás, TA.) Accord. to Ktr, you say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "h`*aA siboTN", "text_ar": "هٰذَا سِبْطٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "h`*ihi siboTN", "text_ar": "هٰذِهِ سِبْطٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "h`w^ulaA='i siboTN", "text_ar": "هٰوُلَا=ءِ سِبْطٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and using"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sbT", "text_ar": "سبط"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as a pl., meaning"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "firoqapN", "text_ar": "فِرْقَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (TA.) The saying"}, {"kind": "quote", "text": "kaA^an~ahu siboTN mina AlA^asobaATi"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is [asserted to be] a mistake, inasmuch as its author imagined that"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "siboTN", "text_ar": "سِبْطٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "meant"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a man:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M:) IDrd ascribes it to El-'Ajjáj or Ru-beh: it occurs in an"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^urojuwzap", "text_ar": "اُرْجُوزَة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "by the latter. (Sgh, TA.) [But it is applied to a single man: for] it is said in a trad., (TA,)"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HusayonN siboTN mina AlA^asobaATi", "text_ar": "حُسَيْنٌ سِبْطٌ مِنَ الاَسْبَاطِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Hoseyn is"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[as though he were]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a nation of the nations"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^um~apN mina", "text_ar": "اُمَّةٌ مِنَ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlA^umami", "text_ar": "الاُمَمِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "K)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in goodness;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "so expl. by Aboo-Bekr: (TA:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "one of the fathers of tribes;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "because of the multitude of his descendants: or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "one of the sons of daughters."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(So in a marginal note in a copy of the “ Jámi' es-Sagheer ” of Es-Suyootee.) ―         -b3-  Also"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A generation"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaron", "text_ar": "قَرْن"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ")"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "that comes after another."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Zj, TA.)       -A2-  And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "siboTN riboEiy~apN", "text_ar": "سِبْطٌ رِبْعِيَّةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (TA in the present art. and in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rbE", "text_ar": "ربع"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ",) or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "riboEiy~apN", "text_ar": "رِبْعِيَّةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "sabaTN", "text_ar": "سَبَطٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (so accord. to a copy of the M, in the present art.,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A palmtree of which the fruit ripens in the end of the summer,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "hot-season."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M, TA.)"}], "source_refs": ["M", "TA", "Msb", "K", "S", "Akh", "Zj"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}